title: Masterpieces in the Museum of Primitive Art (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Pdf | Eng | 1965 | 159 pag | 21.6 MB

The Museum of Primitive Art has rapidly become established as among the most important collections in the world of the indigenous art of Africa, of North and South America, and the islands of the Pacific.
All areas outside the influence of Western culture, they have produced a vast range of styles which have only in recent years been given the serious consideration and study they merit. At the same time appreciation of their aesthetic qualities has heightened into an awareness of the richness of the experience they offer the art-lover. Presented here is a selection from works now in The Museum of Primitive Art, which both demonstrates the scope of the collection, and of these great art-forms themselves
